Description:
The South Yarra Way To Win
The enviable, leafy environs of Rockley Road provide the perfect context for this inviting apartment's impressively renovated spaces where quality has clearly been the priority and comfort is delivered free from compromise. From the timber tones of its floors to its cool colours and flawless presentation, the living/dining area conveys instant appeal - complemented by a contemporary kitchen with an island bench extended so that efficiency and elegance are maximized. Two double bedrooms offering desirable accommodation share a bathroom appointed with the distinctive sense if style that is this apartment's hallmark while natural light, pleasing privacy and allocated car parking complete a superb South Yarra picture close to Chapel Street, trams, trains, the river and Como Park.

Description:
A 'Rise' Above the Rest
With the health and well-being of our community being front of mind we have additional measures in place at all property inspections. Our COVID-19 conditions of entry are available for your viewing click here: https://bit.ly/347XJd6
In the highly sought after "Keilor Village" this three bedroom three bathroom residence presents charm and character throughout with brick walls, slate floors and vaulted ceilings whilst still leaving opportunities to make it truly your own. The kitchen includes a four burner gas stove, oven and dishwasher which leads into the dining and one of two living areas complete with wet bar and cellar. An additional lounge with fire place boasts a balcony with views of the surrounding area, while a dedicated study and rumpus room would suit a variety of purposes. Bedrooms have built in robes master bedroom with ensuite while the family bathroom enjoys a deep soaker bath. Lovely private outdoor entertaining area and children's cubby house, separate studio amongst mature trees make a delightful backyard. Double remote integrated garage, refrigerated cooling, ducted heating, garden shed. Surrounded by bike/walking trails, nearby popular cafes and eateries, local shopping, schools and amenities with easy access to the freeway, airports and city.

Description:
Stylish Spaces On A True Family Scale
With the health and well-being of our community being front of mind we have additional measures in place at all property inspections. Our COVID-19 conditions of entry are available for your viewing click here: https://go.aws/2Z5oMmV
Tell your friends: the perfect place to host gatherings you'll always remember, this five bedroom, three bathroom home located in a quiet court location within Calder Rise Estate has been designed with lots of space for harmonious family living enhanced by contemporary appointments and superb presentation. Beginning with an open living and dining, or living and family if you prefer, it also boasts a quality kitchen/meals area featuring stainless steel appliances, soft - close pale white cabinetry and cool stone countertops. Beyond a sliding glass door a supremely spacious covered entertainer's deck awaits, promising brilliant barbecues and birthdays to come. The 4 downstairs bedrooms (including a master with updated en-suite and WIR) surround a fully tiled central family bathroom with deep freestanding bath. Upstairs, a vast and versatile rumpus with bar offers mountain views , plus the second master bedroom with elegant modern en-suite and large BIR. Also offering video intercom, keyless entry, heating, cooling, ample storage, rainwater tank, extended driveway, carport, automatic double garage and shed, it's seconds to transport and Calder Rise Park and a short drive to Keilor Village, Freeway access and schools, including Overnewton College

Description:
Architecturally Inspired Family Living at its Best
Due to Melbourne's Stage 4 restrictions, the Brad Teal team is working from home and is available via mobile, direct lines, email and even virtually. As private inspections are not currently permitted, please contact our team to discuss your options to view this property virtually.
Welcome home to this inspirational, four bedroom, three bathroom family opportunity with architecturally designed high ceilings, grand spiral staircase and separate living zones. The first level provides room for family entertainment with light filled kitchen, separate meals/dining area, living room and lounge, all leading out to a magnificent outdoor balcony with sweeping views of the valley. The modern kitchen provides 90cm stainless steel gas/electric Smeg stove, Bosch dishwasher, lots of cupboards and bench space, along with huge bi-fold windows out to the balcony. Also on this level are three large bedrooms with built in robes, joined by a common area and large central bathroom with separate shower and a shower bath. The ground level presents a totally self-contained private retreat for parents, or visitors, with master bedroom, separate bathroom, lounge/dining/TV area and generous bar, looking out to a second alfresco patio and garden. With a massive laundry and storage/work room, dual carport, timber floors, intercom system, air-conditioning, ceiling fans, ducted heating and down lights; close to shops, schools and sporting facilities, this is family living at its best.

Description:
Architectural Delight In Sought After Location
Due to Melbourne's Stage 4 restrictions, the Brad Teal team is working from home and is available via mobile, direct lines, email and even virtually. As private inspections are not currently permitted, please contact our team to discuss your options to view this property virtually.
Architecturally designed, this three bedroom, two bathroom and study split-level family home features timber-lined cathedral ceilings overlooking the tranquil environment of Brimbank Park. The open-planned home, designed for entertaining, offers a separate formal lounge/dining room, a magnificent family/living area with built-in Regency gas log fire, split system unit and floor to ceiling windows allowing natural light and panoramic views of the parklands with an adjoining executive private home office/library. The modern light-filled kitchen and meals area comes with an impressive granite island breakfast bar, stainless steel appliances including electric Westinghouse wall oven and separate gas cooktop, Asko dishwasher, pull-out two-door pantry, store room, granite bench tops and splash back with ample drawer and cupboard space. All bedrooms are fully carpeted with mirrored built-in robes in bedrooms 2 and 3, master has a split system unit, open robe and walk through to private fully tiled ensuite with frameless glass shower, marble vanity and IXLTastic light/heat lamp. The main bathroom has a spa bath with overhead shower, marble vanity bench top and fully tiled ceramic floor and wall tiles. The peaceful rustic oasis of a timber decked terrace adjoins the family room by way of bi-fold timber doors to provide an indoor-outdoor setting overlooking a superb built-in pool and spa, park views and surrounded with brick pavers and landscaped garden. Other features include exposed brick feature walls, polished timber floors, ducted heating, evaporative cooler, paved driveway, double carport and paths, plus a splendid native garden. Close to Keilor Village shops, schools and all recreational facilities, this property offers inspirational living or an astute investment.

Description:
Lifestyle On The Village Hill.
With panoramic views over Keilor Village and beyond, this tri-level architecturally designed home will unquestionably satisfy the most discerning of buyers. Features: 4 bedrooms, master with large spa ensuite & walk in robe, formal lounge and dining, home cinema room, fully equipped office/study, plus modern kitchen with granite benchtop and adjoining meals area and family room, wine storage cellar/store room, home gymnasium. Enjoy the sparkling in-ground salt water pool with solar heating, alfresco entertaining area with BBQ and wood fire pizza oven. Includes: gas ducted heating, refrigerated split systems throughout, coonara, vacuum, double auto garage plus endless storage options. Magnificent views from main living areas and balconies, in a premium location with all of the Village amenities close by. It's a beautiful property.

A sizeable block of land, approximately 654m2, in a sought after Keilor neighbourhood, plays host to this immediately comfortable three bedroom, two bathroom single storey brick home offering potential to make it your own. Feel at home in this charming three bedroom, two bathroom English Tudor style unit; situated in a picturesque private enclave at the end of a quiet court. Ideally located within walking distance to main shopping strip, schools and transport. This is a charming English Tudor style unit that will make you feel right at home.

Description:
WHERE DO I SIGN'
Like flicking through the pages of a glossy magazine! Tucked away in one of Keilors prestigious location is a home to put on the top of your priority list. You will find the perfect family living only moments away from quality primary and secondary schools, only a short distance to Overnewton College and St Augustines Primary, Calder Freeway, public transport, local shops (Keilor Village), Calder Rise Neighbourhood Park and so much more. This outstanding home is unquestionably something you would be proud to call home.
Features Include:
Master bedroom showcasing a private balcony, walk-in wardrobe, ensuite with double vanity, 40mm caeser stone bench, floor to ceiling tiles and quality fittings
Additional two spacious bedrooms both with walk-in wardrobes
Study space
The open plan kitchen is located perfectly to incorporate the meals and family area allowing ample space for entertaining which leads out to a gorgeous outdoor area with timber decking and an inbuilt BBQ
Kitchen complete with 40mm caesar stone bench tops, mirror splash back, ample cupboard space, first class stainless steel appliances including 900mm gas cook top, electric oven, dishwasher, inbuilt microwave and double sink
Central bathroom with bathtub, shower, floor to ceiling tiles, 40mm caeser stone bench and quality fittings
Square set cornices, zoned refrigerated cooling and ducted heating, high ceilings, downstairs powder room and alarm system
Polished timber floorboards
Three toilets
Double car garage on remote with internal access
(Photo ID is Required at all Open For Inspections, Prior to Entry)
At YPA Caroline Springs Our Service Will Move You
DISCLAIMER: Every precaution has been taken to establish the accuracy of the above information but it does not constitute any representation by the vendor or agent/agency.
COVID-19 OPEN HOME POLICY
We are still conducting our business but with the safety & health of others and our team are the Highest Priority. Opens homes will consist of the following precautions for everyones safety, hand sanitizer, gloves and masks will be available prior to entry and if requested will be required to be worn prior to entering.
We ask anyone that has recently returned from overseas and if you are unwell to ensure you please do not attend an open home or private inspection.
We thank everyone for their co-operation during this time and please Stay Safe!

Description:
Its all about Space
Found in security of a court location & spread over 4 levels, this home is designed for those that require space. On the lowest level we find a 4-car garage which walks into a Gym or workshop area. The 3rd level we find a superb games room complete with PFB and built in bar. The 2nd level consists of a formal lounge area with a feature stone wall, a large separate dining area both highlighted by the warm of the PFBs.
The kitchen is bright and offers plenty of cupboards and bench space. Adjacent to the kitchen is a large family room and meals area. The upper level shows off 3 spacious bedrooms all with BIRs. Master has a spacious ensuite and WIR. Plus a Study. At the rear of the property we find a lovely undercover pergola area which overlooks a stunning in ground pool. An inspection is a must to fully appreciate this home.

Description:
EXPRESSIONS OF INTEREST - CLOSING 28TH MAY AT 4PM
Please register your interest in attending the open for inspection so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations.
Commanding spectacular outlooks, generous inviting living and sophisticated contemporary updates combine to create an outstanding family residence. Ideally situated on a peaceful cul de sac, lush garden surrounds and an elevated position highlight the tranquillity of the home. A north facing formal living area is complemented by a relaxed retreat with stunning marble open fireplace, looking out to the verdant backyard with pool, spa, courtyard and inbuilt barbecue for alfresco dining and entertaining. A sizeable well appointed kitchen with dining space features quality appliances including gas cooktop, oven and dishwasher. A versatile study is cleverly illuminated by skylights to maximise natural light. Four generous bedrooms including ensuite main with private north facing balcony are equipped with robes, accompanied by a central bathroom with bath and separate rain shower. A laundry with storage and secure double garage completes the residence. Enjoy the convenience of close proximity to Keilor Village life, with restaurants and cafes including local favourite Sweet Lulus Cafe, excellent schooling such as Keilor Primary School, Penleigh and Essendon Grammar Senior School and Overnewton College and parks including Brimbank Park, Joe Brown Recreation Reserve and Lagoon Reserve in easy walking distance.

Description:
A Unique, Lifestyle Opportunity
Please register your interest in attending the open for inspection so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations.
Please also register your interest to attend the auction so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations and be contacted in the event the property is going to be sold prior.
Here is the ultimate dream lifestyle, combining country living and close proximity to the city. Located in the prestigious Keilor Valley, this beautiful home comes complete with Maribyrnong River frontage, superb valley and city skyline views. Single level and with a versatile floor plan, this spacious home comprises 4 large bedrooms, office/5th bedroom, dual bathrooms, multiple living zones, and in the centre hub of home, a lovely updated kitchen to cook up a storm, with huge pantry to store all your essentials and more. Imagine enjoying breakfast on the open alfresco, just so you can soak in the amazing views and take a breath of fresh country air, and at night just huddle up around the exquisite wood fire heater and enjoy this tranquil atmosphere. Features Split system heating/cooling, cosy wood fire heater, polished hardwood timber floors, remote double garage, privacy fencing and exclusive river access. Located approx. 20km radius to Melbourne CBD, and on some 12.5 Acres of natural bushland, this is the change you have been looking for. Seize the opportunity!!

If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Thank you.

Description:
Expansive & Elegant Family Living
Barely a few months old, this vast, versatile and very well appointed family home flaunts five bedrooms, four living spaces and three bathrooms. Uncompromisingly large rooms maximising family harmony include a lounge, bright open kitchen/dining/family, home theatre and retreat with front balcony. Immediately ready to host relaxed alfresco dining, a covered entertaining area sits amidst plentiful open space forming a blank canvas to landscape to your liking. A 90cm stainless steel gas stove, matching canopy rangehood, extensive soft close cabinetry, expansive stone countertops and walk-in pantry define the dream kitchen. Four big bedrooms boast walk-in robes (fifth with built-in robe), including a main with its own balcony, twin robes and ensuite. Completed by a separate bathroom on each of the two storeys, ducted heating, refrigerated cooling, central vacuum, hard wearing timber flooring, data cabling, a wide driveway and triple garage, it's a beautiful base just a stroll to transport and Taylors Creek Linear Park, close to Overnewton College, freeway access and shops.
